{
  "answer": "**The ghazal in chapter 168 of *Diwan-E-Ghalib* begins with the *matla* (opening couplet):**\n\n> Rahiye ab aisi jagah chal kar jahan koi na ho  \n> Hum-sukhan koi na ho aur hum-zuban koi na ho  \n> \n> [Original][^1] | [Transliteration][^2] | [Translation][^3]\n\n**The second couplet (*sher*) after the *matla* is:**\n\n> Be-dar-o-deewar sa ek ghar banaya chahiye  \n> Koi humsaya na ho aur pasban koi na ho\n\n> [Original][^4] | [Transliteration][^5] | [Translation][^6]\n\nThis expresses the poet's desire for utter solitude, imagining a doorless, wall-less house without neighbors or guards.[^7]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 168 [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/168-rahiye-ab-aisi-jagah-chal-kar-jahan-koi-na-ho/original/#p-6df48f).\n\n[^2]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 168 [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/168-rahiye-ab-aisi-jagah-chal-kar-jahan-koi-na-ho/transliteration/#p-6ea3f2).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 168 [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/168-rahiye-ab-aisi-jagah-chal-kar-jahan-koi-na-ho/translation/#p-3a3448).\n\n[^4]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 168 [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/168-rahiye-ab-aisi-jagah-chal-kar-jahan-koi-na-ho/original/#p-a28967).\n\n[^5]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 168 [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/168-rahiye-ab-aisi-jagah-chal-kar-jahan-koi-na-ho/transliteration/#p-198d6d).\n\n[^6]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 168 [paragraph](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/168-rahiye-ab-aisi-jagah-chal-kar-jahan-koi-na-ho/translation/#p-09bdfe).\n\n[^7]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 168 [full chapter (translation)](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/168-rahiye-ab-aisi-jagah-chal-kar-jahan-koi-na-ho/translation/).",
